ey forge new identities, friendships, and job opportunities, giving themselves a renewed sense of self-worth and community. As the United States becomes increasingly polarized over issues of immigration and culture, Fútbol in the Park offers a close look at the individual lives and experiences of migrants.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aHispanic American menxSocial life and customszCalifornia, Southern. 0aHispanic American menxSocial networkszCalifornia, Southern. 0aHispanic American menzCalifornia, SouthernxSocial life and customs. 0aHispanic American men-California, Southern-Social life and customs. 0aHispanic American men-Social networks-California, Southern. 0aHispanic AmericansxSocializationzCalifornia, Southern. 0aHispanic Americans-Socialization-California, Southern. 0aSoccerxSocial aspectszCalifornia, Southern. 0aSoccer-Social aspects-California, Southern. 0aSocial interactionzCalifornia, Southern. 0aSocial interaction-California, Southern. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  a1.  a2.  a3.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021 Englishz978311075418608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021z9783110753967oZDB-23-DSL08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073919040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226748917423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226748917/original  a978-3-11-073919-0  University of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021